  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Consider the set $S(r)$ of points ($x$,$y$) with integer coordinates satisfying $|x| + |y| ≤ r$.</p>\n<p>Let $O$ be the point (0,0) and $C$ the point ($\\frac{r}{4}$,$\\frac{r}{4}$).</p>\n<p>Let $N(r)$ be the number of points $B$ in $S(r)$, so that the triangle $OBC$ has an obtuse angle, i.e. the largest angle $α$ satisfies $90°&#x3C;α&#x3C;180°$.</p>\n<p>So, for example, $N(4)=24$ and $N(8)=100$.</p>\n<p>What is $N(1\\,000\\,000\\,000)$?</p>\n</section>",
